[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      minimum, state-specific medical-record rules,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      institutional-policy retention, FDA SaMD post-market │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      obligations where applicable, and litigation-hold    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      obligations                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - 42 CFR Part 2 retention for substance-use-treatment  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      data                                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - State-specific mental-health retention where         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      relevant                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Outcome correlation as long-time-horizon commitment]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Closed-loop completion rate                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Time-to-resolution for open items                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Referral conversion rate                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Appointment completion rate                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Prior-authorization approval rate and time-to-       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      approval                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Post-discharge follow-up completion rate             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Readmission rate (engaged vs reference cohort)       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - ED-utilization rate                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient-experience metrics                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-manager case-load extension                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort outcome disparities                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort engagement, attrition, completion rates   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-episode-type performance                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Federated-integration availability and latency       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool-call success rates                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stalled-item rate                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-manager escalation rate                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Document-extraction error rate                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical-quality review]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of escalations,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      stalled items, and low-confidence interactions       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers tag failure modes                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Playbook revisions driven by review findings with    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      clinical-leadership sign-off                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    playbook-revision proposals]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Episode state as architectural primitive.** The episode is the unit of state. The episode-state-machine engine is queried and updated on every relevant interaction. Skip the episode model and the bot becomes a context-window-bound chatbot.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-organization federated-state integration.** The bot operates across multiple organizations' systems. Per-organization-pair integration topology, with FHIR APIs preferred, HL7 v2 supported, point-to-point integrations supported, and gracefully-degraded experience where no integration is available.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Closed-loop tracking subsystem.** Every operational item is tracked from creation to resolution. When items stall, the bot follows up. The closed-loop discipline distinguishes coordination from reminder-issuing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Consent-gated multi-audience visibility.** Patient, caregivers (with consent), care team across organizations (with per-organization consent), and care managers each have audience-appropriate views.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-manager workflow integration.** The licensed care-management workforce is a primary system component. The escalation pipeline includes full episode and conversation context.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Document-extraction support.** Document upload is a routine input modality. The OCR and extraction pipelines from chapter 1 are integrated.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation grounding.** Operational claims are grounded in tool-call results. Federated-state syntheses surface sources and timestamps. Conflicts are surfaced rather than papered over.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When the bot is uncertain, when federated sources conflict, when the patient's situation has clinical components, the response defaults to "let me connect you with a person."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring.** Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When federated systems are unreachable, the bot degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior preserves the patient's access to crisis resources, the care-manager escalation pathway, and the patient's own direct contact information for clinicians.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
